description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a workstream configuration analyst to support IM&amp;T with the EPR programme. The successful candidate will need an understanding of the project and the associated timelines. They will be responsible for the collection of necessary content for the configuration of the system using data collection workbooks and the decision design matrices. The analyst will report to the appropriate workstream lead and help manage the risks and deliverables for the workstream. They will also be expected to support testing cycles and act as a super user during the go-live period.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The workstream requiring a configuration analysts in this programme is Patient Flow. This will transform the way West Herts cares for patients and hep deliver efficiencies in the operation of the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate is required to be able demonstrate the Trust values, the responsibilitiesof the job description and person specification. In particular you should have proven experience of working with digital solutions, ideally in one of the above workstreams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is fixed term as only required for the life of the project. This is expected to be until March 2022.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The EPR team via: &lt;/span&gt;westherts.eprprogramme@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
